gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Pelicans 138, Raptors 100
gameRecap.excerpt: The Pelicans defeated the Raptors, 138-100. Brandon Ingram led the way for the Pelicans with a season-high 41 points (20 in the third quarter), along with a career-high eight 3PM, while CJ McCollum added 20 points and six 3PM in the victory. Scottie Barnes tallied 17 points, five rebounds and four assists for the Raptors in the losing effort. The Pelicans win their third straight game as they improve to 29-21 on the season, while the Raptors fall to 17-33.
